        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ajnæg" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d3233e66" type="lemma"><orth>ajnæg</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3233e69"><sense xml:id="sense_d3233e70"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>гладкий</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>smooth</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3233e79"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>гладкая поверхность</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>smooth surface</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3233e88"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>утес</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>cliff</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3233e97"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>отвесная, гладкая скала</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>smooth sheer cliff</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re xml:id="re_d3233e107">
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">Значение ‘гладкий’ устанавливается на
                        основании случаев адъективного употребления этого слова: </note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">The meaning ‘smooth’ is based on the
                        adjectival use of the word: </note>
                    <re xml:id="re_d3233e115">
                        <form xml:id="form_d3233e117" type="lemma"><orth>ajnæg kʼæʒæx</orth></form>
                        <sense xml:id="sense_d3233e120"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>отвесный, гладкий утес</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>sheer, smooth cliff</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re xml:id="re_d3233e131" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <lang/>
                        <form xml:id="form_d3233e135" type="lemma"><orth>ajnæg ex</orth></form>
                        <sense xml:id="sense_d3233e138"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>гладкий лед</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>glaze ice</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d3233e150">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3233e152">
                        <quote>dæ ajnæg kʼæʒæxæj… qūsyn qærzyn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>из твоей отвесной скалы слышу стон</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I hear a groan from your sheer cliff</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>42</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3233e171">
                        <quote>zymty æxsītt ajnægæj ajnægmæ saw kæmtty xæsta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>свист горных индеек оглашал темные ущелья от утеса к утесу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the whistle of snowcocks filled the dark gorges from cliff to
                                cliff</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>121</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3233e190">
                        <quote>jæ alyvars karst ajnæg kʼæʒæx</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кругом — отвесная (как бы) рассеченная скала</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there is a sheer (sort of) cut rock around here</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>128</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3233e209" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>wæd ku raxawuj ainægi bunmæ Wæxadægi furt i mingi Gujman</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>тогда падает к подножию утеса сын Уахадага маленький Гуйман</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>then falls to the foot of the cliff little Guiman, the son of
                                Wakhadag</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>88</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3233e231" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>Aǧundæ ræsuǧd bærzond ajnægæj æ ræsuǧd cæstæj næ rafælgæsuj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>красавица Агунда с высокого утеса прелестным оком не взглянет
                                вниз</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the beauty Agunda will not look down with a lovely eye from a high
                                cliff</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>54%l15-16%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3233e254" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ajnæg exaw gurdæj kʼax</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>нога скользила, как по гладкому льду</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the leg was sliding as it were on smooth ice</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>III
                            36</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3233e276" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>cʼæx ajnæg exbæl kinæ kud zela…</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>как вертится волчок на гладком синем льду…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>like a top spinning on smooth blue ice…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1949 II
                            33</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Слово сближается с <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e353" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e301" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āyīna</w>
                        <gloss><q>зеркало</q></gloss></mentioned> (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ajdæn"/>), но, по-видимому, через тюркское посредство; в
                    тюркских языках мы находим адъективное употребление со значением ‘гладкий’;
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e363" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e311" xml:lang="kk"><lang/>
                        <w>aina baš</w>
                        <gloss><q>гладкая, плешивая голова</q></gloss></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e371" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e319" xml:lang="kk"><lang/>
                        <w>ainala</w>
                        <gloss><q>полировать</q></gloss></mentioned> (ibid. 18). Наращение -<hi rendition="#rend_italic">g</hi>,
                    если оно не произошло на осетинской почве, также может объясняться тюркским
                    посредством, ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e379" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e327" xml:lang="kk"><lang/>
                        <w>aināk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e385" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e333" xml:lang="kk"><w>ainag</w>
                        <gloss><q>окно</q></gloss></mentioned> и др.; ср., впрочем, и на иранской
                    почве <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e391" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e339" xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>ainek</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (с персидского)</note>
                        <gloss><q>зеркало</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The word is close to <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e301" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e353" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āyīna</w>
                        <gloss><q>mirror</q></gloss></mentioned> (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ajdæn"/>), but, apparently, through Turkic; in Turkic
                    languages there is an adjectival use of this word in the meaning ‘smooth’;
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e311" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e363" xml:lang="kk"><lang/>
                        <w>aina baš</w>
                        <gloss><q>smooth, bald head</q></gloss></mentioned>, cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e319" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e371" xml:lang="kk"><lang/>
                        <w>ainala</w>
                        <gloss><q>smooth (v.)</q></gloss></mentioned> (ibid. 18). The augmentaition
                    of -<hi rendition="#rend_italic">g</hi>, if it did not occur on its own in Ossetic, can also be explained from
                    the Turkic languages, cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e327" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e379" xml:lang="kk"><lang/>
                        <w>aināk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e333" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e385" xml:lang="kk"><w>ainag</w>
                        <gloss><q>window</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.; cf., however, in Iranian
                    languages: <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3233e339" xml:id="mentioned_d3233e391" xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>ainek</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from Persian)</note>
                        <gloss><q>mirror</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
            </entry>
